  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dad\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka further down",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Global rating firm S&P has downgraded Sri Lanka's bond rating to 'D', Reuters reported. A 'D' rating means Sri Lanka will default on bond payments and interest.",
        "Sri Lanka, which defaulted on bonds earlier this year, has so far borrowed US$12 billion from private creditors, according to Reuters.",
        "'D' is the lowest rating given by S&P Company to bonds. 'D' grade bonds belong to the high risk investment zone even though a higher interest rate is offered to attract investors. Some investors are reluctant to invest in 'D' grade bonds due to their high risk."
      ],
